Go, go, my naughty girl, and kiss
the evening star above the lane;
let velvet darkness hold your wish,
let starlight shimmer through your pain.

Go, taste the honey in the air,
the summer’s edge upon your tongue;
with wild abandon, do not care
for rules or roads from which you sprung.

Go, go, my restless, laughing spark,
and kiss the night, and leave your mark.
